%%time
def plot(data_column):


    def tfidf(data_column):
        stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
        tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_df=0.8,
                        min_df = 3,
                        stop_words=frozenset(stop_words)
                        )

        result = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(data_column)

        return result


    def dim_reduction(d):
        from sklearn.decomposition import PCA as p1
        r2 = p1(n_components=5).fit_transform(d.todense())
        embedded = TSNE(n_components=3, perplexity=30).fit_transform(r2)
        return embedded

    final = dim_reduction(tfidf(data_column))
    
    return final

using HashingVectorizer¶

In [ ]:
%%time
def plot(data_column):


    def tfidf(data_column):

        import dask_ml.feature_extraction.text

        vect = dask_ml.feature_extraction.text.HashingVectorizer(
                            stop_words='english')
        X = vect.fit_transform(data_column)
        X = X.persist()
        return X
    

    res = tfidf(data_column)
    print(type(res))

    def dim_reduction(d):
        from sklearn.decomposition import PCA as p1
        r2 = p1(n_components=5).fit_transform(d)
        embedded = TSNE(n_components=3, perplexity=30).fit_transform(r2)
        embedded = embedded.persist()
        return embedded

    final = dim_reduction(res)
    
    return final

def pre(data_column):


    def tfidf(data_column):
        from nltk.corpus import stopwords
        stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
        tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_df=0.8,
                        min_df = 3,
                        stop_words=frozenset(stop_words)
                        )

        result = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(data_column)

        return result
    
    res = tfidf(data_column)

    def dim_reduction(d):
        from sklearn.decomposition import PCA as p1
        r2 = p1(n_components=5).fit_transform(d.todense())
        embedded = TSNE(n_components=3, perplexity=30).fit_transform(r2)
        return embedded

    f = dim_reduction(res)
    
    return f

result_data = pre(df2['sentences'])

3D Scatter plot with umap dimension reduction method¶

In [ ]:
from umap import UMAP
import plotly.express as px


umap_2d = UMAP(n_components=2, init='random', random_state=0)
umap_3d = UMAP(n_components=3, init='random', random_state=0)


stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_df=0.8,
                min_df = 3,
                stop_words=frozenset(stop_words)
                )

res = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(df2['sentences'])

proj_2d = umap_2d.fit_transform(res)
proj_3d = umap_3d.fit_transform(res)

fig_2d = px.scatter(
    proj_2d, x=0, y=1,
    color=df2.jim_crow, labels={'color': 'jim_crow'}
)
fig_3d = px.scatter_3d(
    proj_3d, x=0, y=1, z=2,
    color=df2.jim_crow, labels={'color': 'jim_crow'}
)
fig_3d.update_traces(marker_size=1.5)

fig_2d.show()
fig_3d.show()

tagged_data = [TaggedDocument(words=word_tokenize(term_def.lower()), tags=[i]) for i, term_def in enumerate(list_sen)]
In [ ]:
max_epochs = 10
vec_size = 50
alpha = 0.025

model = Doc2Vec(vector_size=vec_size,
                alpha=alpha, 
                min_alpha=0.00025,
                min_count=2,
                dm=1)
  
model.build_vocab(tagged_data)
In [ ]:
for epoch in range(max_epochs):
    if epoch % 10 == 0:
        print('iteration {0}'.format(epoch))

    model.train(tagged_data,
                total_examples=model.corpus_count,
                epochs=model.epochs)
    
    model.alpha -= 0.002
    model.min_alpha = model.alpha

model.save("d2v_do_v100_e10.model")

max_epochs = 10
vec_size = 100
alpha = 0.025

model_sec = Doc2Vec(vector_size=vec_size,
                alpha=alpha, 
                min_alpha=0.00025,
                min_count=2,
                dm=1)
  
model_sec.build_vocab(tagged_sec)

for epoch in range(max_epochs):
    if epoch % 10 == 0:
        print('iteration {0}'.format(epoch))

    model_sec.train(tagged_sec,
                total_examples=model_sec.corpus_count,
                epochs=model_sec.epochs)
    
    model_sec.alpha -= 0.002
    model_sec.min_alpha = model_sec.alpha

model_sec.save("d2v_sectiontext_v100_e10.model")
